CompanyDescription: FS Bancorp, Inc. ("FS Bancorp" or the "Company"), a Washington corporation, was organized in September 2011 for the purpose of becoming the holding company of 1st Security Bank of Washington ("1st Security Bank of Washington" or the "Bank") upon the Bank's conversion from a mutual to a stock savings bank ("Conversion"). The Conversion was completed on July 9, 2012. At December 31, 2019, the Company had consolidated total assets of $1.71 billion, total deposits of $1.39 billion, and stockholders' equity of $200.2 million. The Company has not engaged in any significant activity other than holding the stock of the Bank. Accordingly, the information set forth in this Annual Report on Form 10­K ("Form 10­K"), including the consolidated financial statements and related data, relates primarily to the Bank. 1st Security Bank of Washington is a relationship-driven community bank.  ...
